 "components": {
  "instruction": "Classify the given text into one of these categories: automatic_top_up, balance_not_updated_after_bank_transfer, beneficiary_not_allowed, cancel_transfer, card_payment_fee_charged, card_payment_not_recognised, declined_cash_withdrawal, exchange_rate, exchange_via_app, failed_transfer, get_disposable_virtual_card, get_physical_card, passcode_forgotten, pending_top_up, pending_transfer, receiving_money, reverted_card_payment?, top_up_by_cash_or_cheque, top_up_reverted, topping_up_by_card, transfer_fee_charged, transfer_into_account, transfer_timing, verify_my_identity, verify_source_of_funds.\n\nImportant distinctions to note:\n\n1. **beneficiary_not_allowed vs failed_transfer**: When a user receives a message saying their transfer \"isn't possible\" or they cannot transfer to a specific recipient/beneficiary, this should be classified as 'beneficiary_not_allowed', NOT 'failed_transfer'. The category 'beneficiary_not_allowed' is about restrictions on who can receive money, while 'failed_transfer' is about transfers that were attempted but failed for technical reasons.\n\n2. **reverted_card_payment? vs cancel_transfer**: When a card payment has been cancelled or reversed, this should be classified as 'reverted_card_payment?', NOT 'cancel_transfer'. The category 'cancel_transfer' refers to bank transfers or money transfers between accounts, while 'reverted_card_payment?' specifically deals with card payments that have been reversed or cancelled.\n\n3. **top_up_reverted vs reverted_card_payment?**: When a top-up (adding money to the account) has been reversed or cancelled by the app/system, this should be classified as 'top_up_reverted', NOT 'reverted_card_payment?'. The category 'top_up_reverted' specifically deals with reversals of money being added to the user's account, while 'reverted_card_payment?' deals with card payments made to merchants or other parties being reversed.\n\n4. **get_physical_card vs passcode_forgotten**: When a user is asking about receiving their PIN number or when they will have access to their PIN, this is about getting a new physical card, so classify as 'get_physical_card', NOT 'passcode_forgotten'. The category 'passcode_forgotten' is specifically for users who have forgotten an existing passcode and need to reset or recover it, while 'get_physical_card' covers questions about receiving a new card and its associated PIN for the first time.\n\n5. Pay close attention to whether the issue involves:\n   - A card payment to a merchant/third party (use 'reverted_card_payment?' for reversals)\n   - A top-up/adding money to the account (use 'top_up_reverted' for reversals, 'pending_top_up' for delays, 'topping_up_by_card' for the process)\n   - A bank transfer or money transfer between accounts (use transfer-related categories)\n   - The identity of the recipient/beneficiary (consider 'beneficiary_not_allowed')\n   - Getting a new card and PIN (use 'get_physical_card')\n   - Forgetting an existing passcode (use 'passcode_forgotten')\n\nRead the text carefully and match it to the most specific and appropriate category based on the exact nature of the customer's issue."
 },
